President Obama spoke with New York Governor Andrew Cuomo and New York City Mayor Bill de Blasio regarding the diagnosis of an Ebola case in New York City. The President commended the preparations made by New York City and Bellevue Hospital Center for this situation. They discussed the deployment of CDC officials to New York City, with additional teams arriving that night. The President offered federal support to ensure the highest standard of patient care, safety protocols for healthcare workers, and monitoring of potential contacts. He expressed his thoughts and prayers for the patient and asked the Governor and Mayor to stay in close contact with his team.